  "concept": "vuejs/core#8342: Report an error when the component event name is once",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:24:32.531139+00:00",
  "text": "Report an error when the component event name is once\n\n### Vue version\n\nlatest\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nopen the link\n\n### What is expected?\n\nno error\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nget error：\r\n`Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'toLowerCase')`\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nIssue exposed by #8334  and doesn't seem to be fixed by #8338",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
